Fetch COVID Hospitalization Data by State

Source: R/endpoints.R
covid_hosp_state_timeseries.Rd

Obtains the COVID-19 reported patient impact and hospital capacity data by state. This dataset is provided by the US Department of Health & Human Services via healthdata.gov.

covid_hosp_state_timeseries(states, dates, issues = NULL)

Arguments

states

A two letter character string state abbreviation.

dates

Takes in the form epirange(startdate,enddate), where startdate and enddate are of the form YYYYMMDD (can be passed as string or numeric).

issues

An optional parameter that takes the form YYYYMMDD. If issues is not specified, then the most recent issue is used by default.

Value

an instance of epidata_call

Details

Starting October 1, 2022, some facilities are only required to report annually.

References

API Documentation: https://cmu-delphi.github.io/delphi-epidata/api/covid_hosp.html.

See also the official description and data dictionary at <healthdata.gov> for more information.

Examples

# \donttest{
call <- covid_hosp_state_timeseries(states = "fl", dates = epirange(20200101, 20200501))
fetch_csv(call)
